Parliament, Tuesday, 20 November 2018 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow (Wednesday, 21 November 2018) be briefed by National Treasury on the Adjustments Appropriations Bill [B35-2018] and the Department of Public Enterprises on the Special Appropriation Bill [B36-2018]. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 21 November 2018
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Ground Floor, Marks Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA AND MR CHAREL DE BEER. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committees’ Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za Political parties represented in Parliament are entitled to an amount of public money for their political activities. The parties receive the money in proportion to the number of seats they hold.Read more